issue.body: Fix for the issue I brought up in https://github.com/Koenkk/zigbee2mqtt/issues/15239

issue.title: Support the second button of WDE002906
issue.body: Fix for the issue I brought up in https://github.com/Koenkk/zigbee2mqtt/issues/15239

comment.body: The code you pasted also has the flaw that even though the device apparently exposes endpoints 23 and 24, they are not really used and should not be published.

issue.title: Support the second button of WDE002906
issue.body: Fix for the issue I brought up in https://github.com/Koenkk/zigbee2mqtt/issues/15239

comment.body:
I have the device and I have tested this. I am a recent migrant from ZHA to this device and previously created a Gist for HA with the same configuration:

https://gist.github.com/ferrix/ca7cda4c3b808419d0d6d52317e3a807

I did it there using the template for 'FLS/AIRLINK/4'.

https://community.home-assistant.io/t/schneider-wiser-remote/407990

My implementation is an adaptation of the AIRLINK version from the same schneider.js file and there IS the battery but only for the left button or endpoint 21 since there is no use duplicating it (and I am not actually sure if the device supports it in the other endpoints)
